The paper proposes a deep learning approach for multi-step forecasting of blood glucose levels, which is a clinically relevant task. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep architectures and modeling of the distribution of future values also suggests that the paper may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on a specific application (blood glucose forecasting) may suggest that the paper belongs to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category.
